flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Determine And Simulate Scenarios (scheduled planning cycle or event-driven: forecast deviation, inventory shortage, or executive directive)]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Consolidate master and transaction inputs]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Remote Functions - Generate baseline update and candidate scenario set]
  N2 --> N3{PB: Rules - Select scenarios for execution}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[Cortex: Remote Functions - Run multi-scenario supply simulations]
  N4 --> N5[PB: CWB Lifecycle - Finalize and capture decision]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Remote Functions - Execute selected plan and notify stakeholders]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced stockouts and lost revenue, improved working capital utilization, faster decision cycle with auditable rationale for selected supply options, and automated execution of supply plan changes.]
  N3 -->|Simulation results exceed revenue-los...| B1[Trigger CWB Lifecycle with escalation to planning leads and generate alternate high-cost expedite scenarios (use Remote Functions to model expedited options)]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Human-in-the-loop approves expedited actions to protect revenue; increased cost vs. revenue trade-off documented]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Critical input data missing or failin...| B2[Pause process (Process Builder Wait), send Data Quality notification to data stewards, and block simulations until resolved]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Simulations deferred; data corrected and re-ingested with full audit trail to ensure decision integrity]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Multiple scenarios present near-equal...| B3[Surface ranked scenarios in a dashboard / UI screen for planner selection and record selection via CWB Lifecycle]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Planner selects preferred scenario; decision captured for audit and executed via Remote Functions]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]